{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VYKngnTJdnZHtRuFaMzUBf","type":"tool_result","content":"/workspace/docs/workflows.md:| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md:resolution order is: step-level > workflow-level block > `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md:runs `main` with `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` set, then runs `finalize` regardless of outcome.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md:The `list-tasks` script writes one JSON object per line to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`.\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md:`CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars).\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md:runs via the daemon's standard run pipeline. Environment variables (`CLOCHE_TASK_ID`,\n/workspace/docs/workflows.md:`CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, etc.) are injected into each step; `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` still\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:For example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — try next command\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** — use that result (no fallback)\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:set in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:The `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:workflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Working directory (set for script steps so `cloche get`/`cloche set` work). |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:Show per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n/workspace/docs/USAGE.md:the `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JL8mFVY8Rhg22KuPsWEiLJ","session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"a946ca8a-7ef3-4266-b131-91cf2ed5a7f7"}
