{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MkpDGK51diLNErPSrhpeDF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Next Features\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→## Orchestration\n     5→\n     6→We need an orchestrator - a program whose task it is to grab the next \"ready\" ticket (from beads currently, but we'll need to \n     7→wrap it in a general adapter for \"task tracking\" services, so that we can add later support for Jira, Linear, github issues, \n     8→etc) and then generate an appropriate prompt (using the host's code agent) before kicking off `cloche run`. \n     9→\n    10→If `cloched`/`cloche-agent` are the workers in a factory, the orchestrator is the energy. It ensures the system continues to\n    11→run, delivering work to the system so long as any is available.\n    12→\n    13→When started, it checks for any unblocked / ready work to begin.\n    14→\n    15→`cloched` then kicks off the orchestrator (with the appropriate project context) whenever a task completes successfully.\n    16→\n    17→## Indicator lights\n    18→\n    19→If cloche is a factory, we need indicator lights to show when things are running well and when they are not.\n    20→\n    21→## Web Dashboard\n    22→\n    23→The main landing page dashboard should show each known project with indicator lights for status.\n    24→\n    25→## Log contents\n    26→\n    27→We need to capture _all_ output from each prompt and script, not just status changes. This will give us a log of the LLM's thoughts\n    28→and the scripts output to help reconstruct any issues post-facto.\n    29→\n    30→## Container deletion\n    31→\n    32→Don't auto-delete the containers from failed tasks. We may need them to investigate issues.\n    33→Show all kept containers in the web dashboard (and cli tool) with an option to delete them (cli: cloche delete <container name>)\n    34→\n    35→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JL8mFVY8Rhg22KuPsWEiLJ","session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"8a2624f9-dca6-464d-b31b-7485d36b3899"}
