{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JL8mFVY8Rhg22KuPsWEiLJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Exploration Summary: Cloche Codebase Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here's a comprehensive report covering all requested areas:\n\n### 1. Documentation Files Structure\n\n**Key Documentation Files:**\n- `/workspace/README.md` - Main project overview\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` - Project guidance for Claude Code\n- `/workspace/AGENTS.md` - Agent workflow instructions\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - Workflow DSL syntax and semantics\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` - Complete CLI reference and project layout\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md` - Installation instructions\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - Overall architecture\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md` - MVP implementation details\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` - Host workflow executor design\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md` - Docker base image design\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md` - Project initialization\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md` - Configuration file format\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md` - Step timeout feature\n\n### 2. Docker Configuration\n\n**Dockerfile Locations:**\n- `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` - Base image with `cloche-agent` and Git\n- `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile` - Cloche project's own container (builds on cloche-base)\n- `/workspace/examples/gemini-browser/Dockerfile` - Example project (Rust-based)\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/Dockerfile` - Example project (C-based)\n\n**Base Image Content:**\n- Multi-stage build from `golang:1.25` → `debian:12-slim`\n- Includes: `git`, `ca-certificates`, `cloche-agent` binary\n- Creates non-root `agent` user with `/workspace` as working directory\n- Does NOT include language runtimes or build tools (project-specific)\n\n**Container Configuration in Code:**\n- File: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n  - `ContainerConfig` struct with fields: `Image`, `WorkflowName`, `ProjectDir`, `NetworkAllow`, `RunID`, `Cmd`\n  - `ContainerRuntime` interface for start/stop/logs/copy operations\n\n### 3. Network Allowlisting\n\n**Current Status:** DESIGNED BUT NOT YET FULLY IMPLEMENTED\n\n**Design Documentation:**\n- Specified in `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- Network allowlist via `network_allow` configuration key in workflow DSL\n\n**Configuration Example (from workflows.md):**\n```\ncontainer {\n  image = \"my-project:latest\"\n  network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation Status:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`: `NetworkAllow []string` field exists\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`: Currently implements basic docker create/start without network restrictions\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`: Contains TODO comment:\n  ```\n  // TODO: Create custom network with allowlist. For now, use bridge.\n  networkMode = \"bridge\"\n  ```\n- Current workaround: Uses `--network bridge` when allowlist is specified, otherwise `--network none` is default\n\n**Planned Implementation:**\n- Create custom Docker network with DNS proxy\n- Restrict egress to allowlisted domains\n- Currently punted to post-MVP phase\n\n### 4. Container Model & File Isolation\n\n**File Handling:**\n- No bind mounts used; entire project copied via `docker cp` at start\n- `/workspace/` is the container working directory\n- Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` applied on top\n- `.git/` is included in the copy\n- Results extracted via `docker cp` to git branches on host\n\n**Security Boundaries (from system design):**\n1. **Filesystem** - No access beyond `/workspace`\n2. **Network** - Allowlisted (TODO: implement DNS proxy)\n3. **Environment** - Configured in Dockerfile/image only (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY passed through if set)\n\n### 5. Host Workflow Executor\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n**Functionality:**\n- `Executor` struct implements `engine.StepExecutor` interface\n- Executes three step types:\n  1. **Script steps** - Shell commands via `sh -c`, exit codes determine result\n  2. **Workflow steps** - Dispatches container workflows and blocks until completion\n  3. **Agent steps** - Invokes agents on host using prompt adapter\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Output mappings from wire definitions\n- Environment variables injected: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n- Script execution from main git worktree (not linked worktrees)\n- Stores step outputs to files for passing between steps\n\n**File:** `.cloche/host.cloche` - Special workflow file that runs on host, not in container\n\n### 6. AgentAdapter Interface\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n\n**Interface Definition:**\n```go\ntype AgentAdapter interface {\n    Name() string\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, step *domain.Step, workDir string) (result string, err error)\n}\n```\n\n**Implementations:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` - Generic prompt-based adapter\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` - Arbitrary command executor\n\n**Agent Configuration (from USAGE.md):**\n- Priority order:\n  1. Step-level `agent_command`\n  2. Workflow-level config block (`container {}` for container workflows, `host {}` for host)\n  3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n  4. Default: `claude`\n- Fallback chains supported: `agent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"`\n- Result protocol: Print `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker to stdout\n\n### 7. Prompt Usage & Assembly\n\n**Prompt Files:**\n- Location: `.cloche/prompts/*.md` (user-created templates)\n- Accessed via `file(\"path\")` function in DSL, resolved at runtime\n\n**Prompt Assembly (from USAGE.md):**\n1. Step template (inline or `file()` resolved)\n2. User request (from `--prompt` flag → `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`)\n3. Validation output (optional, if `feedback = \"true\"`)\n4. Result selection (instructions to print `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`)\n\n**Host Workflow Prompts:**\n- Generated by scripts in `.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh`\n- Default: Task title + body from task tracking system\n- Written to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` for next step\n\n### 8. Security-Related Configuration\n\n**Filesystem Security:**\n- No bind mounts (isolated copies)\n- Container filesystem limited to `/workspace/`\n- Override files support (`.cloche/overrides/`)\n- Host files never directly accessible\n\n**Environment Security:**\n- Only explicitly set env vars passed to containers\n- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` passed through if set in host environment\n- Extra mounts via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` environment variable\n- Extra env vars via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` environment variable\n\n**Agent Security:**\n- On host: Agent steps run with daemon privileges (safety: use with caution)\n- In container: Runs as unprivileged `agent` user\n- Claude auth files (`.claude`, `.claude.json`) copied (not mounted) to avoid concurrent write conflicts\n\n**Project Safety (from host workflow design):**\n- Host steps run with daemon OS privileges\n- No network isolation on host\n- `host.cloche` should only reference committed scripts\n- Prompt steps in `host.cloche` invoke agents with full host filesystem access\n\n**Container Safety:**\n- Failed runs keep containers for investigation\n- Successful runs clean up containers (unless `--keep-container` flag)\n- Containers inherit permissions set in Dockerfile (`USER agent`)\n\n### 9. Project Configuration\n\n**Configuration File:** `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml` (per project)\n\n**Settings:**\n```toml\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 1\nstagger_seconds = 1.0\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = true\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n```\n\n**Project Layout:**\n```\n.cloche/\n  ├── config.toml          # Project settings\n  ├── version              # Version counter\n  ├── develop.cloche       # Container workflow\n  ├── host.cloche          # Host orchestration\n  ├── Dockerfile           # Container image\n  ├── prompts/             # Prompt templates\n  ├── scripts/             # Host scripts\n  ├── overrides/           # Override files\n  └── <run-id>/            # Runtime artifacts (gitignored)\n```\n\n### 10. Codebase Structure\n\n**Core Architecture (Hexagonal):**\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/` - Domain types (Workflow, Step, Run)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/` - Interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, AgentAdapter)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/` - Implementations:\n  - `docker/` - Docker container runtime\n  - `sqlite/` - SQLite storage\n  - `grpc/` - gRPC server/client\n  - `agents/` - Agent adapters\n  - `web/` - Web dashboard\n  - `local/` - Local subprocess runtime (dev only)\n- `/workspace/internal/dsl/` - Workflow DSL parser\n- `/workspace/internal/engine/` - Graph execution engine\n- `/workspace/internal/host/` - Host workflow executor\n- `/workspace/internal/evolution/` - Self-evolution feature\n- `/workspace/cmd/` - Three binaries:\n  - `cloche/` - CLI client\n  - `cloched/` - Daemon\n  - `cloche-agent/` - In-container agent\n\n**File Paths for Reference:**\n- System design: `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- Implementation details: `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`\n- Docker runtime: `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`\n- Host executor: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n- Container ports: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n- Agent ports: `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go`\n- Workflow DSL: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` (not read, but referenced)\n- Usage guide: `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a03c0cf2f52866738 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71463\ntool_uses: 42\nduration_ms: 114193</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b861655-1988-46e5-92b9-f0a2db90f2de","uuid":"cabbacc4-efcc-497d-80bd-52bc90303c56","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this codebase to understand:\n1. Existing documentation files (docs/ directory, any .md files at the root)\n2. How Docker containers are configured - look at Dockerfiles, container runtime adapters, network configuration\n3. How network allowlisting works\n4. The host workflow executor and how it relates to prompt usage\n5. Any existing security-related configuration or documentation\n\nSearch thoroughly for:\n- docs/**/*.md\n- **/Dockerfile*\n- Any network/allowlist configuration in internal/adapters/docker/\n- Host workflow execution in internal/host/\n- Any mentions of \"allowlist\", \"network\", \"security\", \"safety\" in the codebase\n- The AgentAdapter interface and how agents are configured\n\nReport back with the content/structure of all relevant files.","agentId":"a03c0cf2f52866738","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Exploration Summary: Cloche Codebase Analysis\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here's a comprehensive report covering all requested areas:\n\n### 1. Documentation Files Structure\n\n**Key Documentation Files:**\n- `/workspace/README.md` - Main project overview\n- `/workspace/CLAUDE.md` - Project guidance for Claude Code\n- `/workspace/AGENTS.md` - Agent workflow instructions\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - Workflow DSL syntax and semantics\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` - Complete CLI reference and project layout\n- `/workspace/docs/INSTALL.md` - Installation instructions\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md` - Overall architecture\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md` - MVP implementation details\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` - Host workflow executor design\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-base-docker-design.md` - Docker base image design\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-cloche-init-design.md` - Project initialization\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-config-toml-design.md` - Configuration file format\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-04-step-timeout-design.md` - Step timeout feature\n\n### 2. Docker Configuration\n\n**Dockerfile Locations:**\n- `/workspace/docker/cloche-base/Dockerfile` - Base image with `cloche-agent` and Git\n- `/workspace/.cloche/Dockerfile` - Cloche project's own container (builds on cloche-base)\n- `/workspace/examples/gemini-browser/Dockerfile` - Example project (Rust-based)\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/Dockerfile` - Example project (C-based)\n\n**Base Image Content:**\n- Multi-stage build from `golang:1.25` → `debian:12-slim`\n- Includes: `git`, `ca-certificates`, `cloche-agent` binary\n- Creates non-root `agent` user with `/workspace` as working directory\n- Does NOT include language runtimes or build tools (project-specific)\n\n**Container Configuration in Code:**\n- File: `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`\n  - `ContainerConfig` struct with fields: `Image`, `WorkflowName`, `ProjectDir`, `NetworkAllow`, `RunID`, `Cmd`\n  - `ContainerRuntime` interface for start/stop/logs/copy operations\n\n### 3. Network Allowlisting\n\n**Current Status:** DESIGNED BUT NOT YET FULLY IMPLEMENTED\n\n**Design Documentation:**\n- Specified in `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md`\n- Network allowlist via `network_allow` configuration key in workflow DSL\n\n**Configuration Example (from workflows.md):**\n```\ncontainer {\n  image = \"my-project:latest\"\n  network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation Status:**\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go`: `NetworkAllow []string` field exists\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go`: Currently implements basic docker create/start without network restrictions\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-implementation.md`: Contains TODO comment:\n  ```\n  // TODO: Create custom network with allowlist. For now, use bridge.\n  networkMode = \"bridge\"\n  ```\n- Current workaround: Uses `--network bridge` when allowlist is specified, otherwise `--network none` is default\n\n**Planned Implementation:**\n- Create custom Docker network with DNS proxy\n- Restrict egress to allowlisted domains\n- Currently punted to post-MVP phase\n\n### 4. Container Model & File Isolation\n\n**File Handling:**\n- No bind mounts used; entire project copied via `docker cp` at start\n- `/workspace/` is the container working directory\n- Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` applied on top\n- `.git/` is included in the copy\n- Results extracted via `docker cp` to git branches on host\n\n**Security Boundaries (from system design):**\n1. **Filesystem** - No access beyond `/workspace`\n2. **Network** - Allowlisted (TODO: implement DNS proxy)\n3. **Environment** - Configured in Dockerfile/image only (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY passed through if set)\n\n### 5. Host Workflow Executor\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\n**Functionality:**\n- `Executor` struct implements `engine.StepExecutor` interface\n- Executes three step types:\n  1. **Script steps** - Shell commands via `sh -c`, exit codes determine result\n  2. **Workflow steps** - Dispatches container workflows and blocks until completion\n  3. **Agent steps** - Invokes agents on host using prompt adapter\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Output mappings from wire definitions\n- Environment variables injected: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n- Script execution from main git worktree (not linked